// monitoring/kql/smoke-emit-metric.kql
//
// Smoke-test assertion query (#56). Run against the env's Application Insights resource.
// Returns ONE row with the count of `copilot_byok_*` custom metrics emitted in the
// supplied window. The smoke-test script (scripts/smoke-test.ps1 / .sh) interprets
// `Hits > 0` as PASS and any other result as FAIL.
//
// Why this query is the #16 regression gate:
//   The `emit-metric` policy block is silently no-op'd by APIM when the service-level
//   `applicationinsights` diagnostic doesn't have `properties.metrics: true`. The HTTP
//   path keeps working (200s on chat/completions), tokens are deducted by the model,
//   but the custom metrics never arrive. This query is the only post-deploy signal
//   that catches that regression class. If a future PR drops `metrics: true` from
//   apim.bicep, this query returns 0 and the smoke job goes red.
//
// Why we OR-match the three metric names (not just one):
//   `copilot_byok_request` fires in inbound and is emitted on EVERY call (even when the
//   upstream errors out before tokens flow). `*_prompt_tokens` / `*_completion_tokens`
//   only fire on a 200-class response. By matching any of the three we accept the
//   weakest valid signal -- "at least one request was metered". That's exactly what
//   smoke is asserting.
//
// Inputs (set by the smoke-test caller via `az monitor app-insights query --analytics-query`):
//   - The query is parameterless; the lookback window is hard-coded to 15m so the
//     query is self-contained and re-runnable in the Azure portal.
//
// Tweakables:
//   - Lengthen the lookback (e.g. ago(1h)) when investigating intermittent failures.
//   - Add `| extend env = tostring(customDimensions["env"])` filter once the deploy
//     stamps env name on metrics (TODO, follow-up).
//
// Output schema: a single row `Hits:long, LatestEmit:datetime, DistinctMetricNames:long`.
//   - Hits = total number of metric data-points seen (sum of `valueCount` across rows)
//   - LatestEmit = wall-clock timestamp of the most recent emit (handy for triage)
//   - DistinctMetricNames = how many of the 3 metric names landed (1..3)
//
// Column note: `customMetrics` rows do NOT have an `itemCount` column (that's a
// `traces`/`requests`/`exceptions` thing). The correct aggregate for "how many
// data points landed" is `sum(valueCount)`. Using `sum(itemCount)` here produces
// the App Insights server-side error:
//     SEM0100: 'summarize' operator: Failed to resolve scalar expression named 'itemCount'
// which surfaces from the CLI as `BadArgumentError: The request had some invalid
// properties`. See #60.
customMetrics
| where timestamp > ago(15m)
| where name in ("copilot_byok_request", "copilot_byok_auto_route", "copilot_byok_prompt_tokens", "copilot_byok_completion_tokens")
| summarize
    Hits                = sum(valueCount),
    LatestEmit          = max(timestamp),
    DistinctMetricNames = dcount(name)
